* start game
* create player class
* prompt players for name
* ask how many games they'd like to play
* set code entered from codemaker
  * use IO.Console to hide the entry from codemaker
  * have them enter it twice, to confirm it's correct
* validate code so it can only be a series of 4 numbers 1-6 (print with colors)
* have codebreaker enter guess
* print codebreaker's guess
* show the board with codebreakers's guess
* print extra stuff to the right of the guess
* give feedback for codebreaker's guess
* have 12 rounds of guessing
* check if codebreaker won after each guess
* after 12 rounds end the game and award points based on final outcome
